something like this? 
Temporarily Able-Bodied (TAB) The term Temporarily Able-Bodied (TAB) indicates that many people will become disabled, either temporarily or permanently, at some point in their lives. 
A disability can be the result of injury, illness, age, or circumstance. 
Instances of temporary disabilities (not caused by injury or illness) include: working in a noisy environment, working in environments where noise is not tolerated (e.g., libraries, work cubicles, and at home when children are sleeping), and instances when hands and eyes are busy (e.g., driving a car). 
