I agree with Judy. 
In the first place, I have never heard of TABs, and I suspect that a high proportion of the world's literate population would be in the same situation. 
Secondly, the guidelines would be better without yet another, potentially confusing acronym. 
Finally, the concept of "universal design", which can be easily explained, seems to encompass all of the general principles and policy considerations which motivate this group's work. 
